(Let Hye Yeong's new room
be filled with luck.)

1306
01:02:59,310 --> 01:03:01,550
(Let Hye Yeong's new room
be filled with luck.)

1307
01:03:04,890 --> 01:03:05,890
I love it.

1308
01:03:08,760 --> 01:03:10,730
It could get stuffy
without a window.

1309
01:03:11,930 --> 01:03:13,030
I still love it.

1310
01:03:14,630 --> 01:03:15,700
And...

1311
01:03:16,700 --> 01:03:18,300
Here you go.
These are keys to your door.

1312
01:03:18,930 --> 01:03:20,230
You're a young lady
now that you're in eighth grade,

1313
01:03:20,230 --> 01:03:21,270
so lock your door.

1314
01:03:21,270 --> 01:03:22,340
No one enters
without your permission.

1315
01:03:25,540 --> 01:03:26,910
This is touching.

1316
01:03:27,280 --> 01:03:28,440
Let's applaud, guys.

1317
01:03:28,540 --> 01:03:30,280
Hye Yeong, have a good life.

1318
01:03:30,280 --> 01:03:31,850
- We wish you the best.
- Have a great life.

1319
01:03:31,850 --> 01:03:33,350
Enjoy your new home.

1320
01:03:34,520 --> 01:03:35,720
Hye Yeong, have a good life.

1321
01:03:35,820 --> 01:03:36,950
Enjoy your life.

1322
01:03:36,950 --> 01:03:39,550
- Call us if you need anything.
- Yes, call us.

1323
01:03:48,800 --> 01:03:49,900
Try to get some sleep.

1324
01:03:50,630 --> 01:03:51,700
Just don't snore.

1325
01:03:52,570 --> 01:03:53,570
I'm fine.

1326
01:03:54,070 --> 01:03:55,440
Your eyes are bloodshot.

1327
01:03:56,500 --> 01:03:58,910
Why won't you close your eyes
when you can easily take catnaps?

1328
01:04:01,440 --> 01:04:02,980
You dozing off would be disastrous,

1329
01:04:02,980 --> 01:04:04,010
so I need to watch you.

1330
01:04:05,410 --> 01:04:07,150
Have I ever fallen asleep
behind the wheel?

1331
01:04:11,520 --> 01:04:13,190
You're with the same girl
for longer this time.

1332
01:04:16,820 --> 01:04:17,990
Why do you call her a girl?

1333
01:04:18,490 --> 01:04:20,760
You don't know how old she is.

1334
01:04:21,100 --> 01:04:22,800
What else
should I call your girlfriend?

1335
01:04:24,030 --> 01:04:25,100
Ms. Girlfriend?

1336
01:04:26,170 --> 01:04:28,070
Just call her my girlfriend.

1337
01:04:29,270 --> 01:04:30,570
Why have you been with her
for so long?

1338
01:04:31,110 --> 01:04:32,670
Hasn't it been almost a year now?

1339
01:04:32,670 --> 01:04:34,640
At this rate, you'll be reminding me
of my anniversary.

1340
01:04:36,440 --> 01:04:37,850
It's wrong to date someone
for so long...

1341
01:04:37,850 --> 01:04:38,910
if you don't plan to marry.

1342
01:04:38,910 --> 01:04:40,210
Mind your own business,

1343
01:04:41,080 --> 01:04:42,080
and get some sleep.

1344
01:04:49,520 --> 01:04:51,060
It's kind of my business.

1345
01:04:59,170 --> 01:05:00,330
- Sir.
- Yes?

1346
01:05:01,070 --> 01:05:02,540
What should we get for lunch?

1347
01:05:03,000 --> 01:05:04,010
(Radiant Homes Realtor)

1348
01:05:04,010 --> 01:05:05,010
We'll have that.

1349
01:05:07,280 --> 01:05:08,940
What are the other options?

1350
01:05:09,080 --> 01:05:10,140
This is Lee Ji Hyuk.

1351
01:05:11,980 --> 01:05:13,050
Is there a unit for me?

1352
01:05:17,390 --> 01:05:20,090
There are still a few days left
on the lease,

1353
01:05:20,350 --> 01:05:21,990
but the previous tenant
moved out early...

1354
01:05:21,990 --> 01:05:23,960
to care for their mother.

1355
01:05:24,890 --> 01:05:26,830
This is the best unit
I've seen so far.

1356
01:05:28,460 --> 01:05:29,800
I'll take it.

1357
01:05:29,800 --> 01:05:31,730
That's a wise choice.

1358
01:05:31,900 --> 01:05:34,300
I'll contact the landlord
and set up a meeting.

1359
01:05:35,940 --> 01:05:36,970
Sure.

1360
01:05:36,970 --> 01:05:38,010
(Overseas Travel Package Plan)

1361
01:05:40,070 --> 01:05:42,740
I want to visit every spot
from "Roman Holiday,"

1362
01:05:43,580 --> 01:05:45,950
see Sagrada Familia in Barcelona,

1363
01:05:45,950 --> 01:05:47,050
and as for Paris...

1364
01:05:47,850 --> 01:05:49,220
Do you remember that movie?

1365
01:05:49,280 --> 01:05:51,520
The bridge
from "The Lovers on the Bridge."

1366
01:05:52,350 --> 01:05:55,090
Also, Ethan Hawke was a dream
in "Before Sunrise."

1367
01:05:55,290 --> 01:05:56,790
I've been wanting to see Vienna too.

1368
01:05:57,830 --> 01:06:00,030
You're right. When we were young,

1369
01:06:00,030 --> 01:06:02,260
we dreamed of European cities
from the movies we watched.

1370
01:06:03,330 --> 01:06:05,300
Pick one country you want to visit,

1371
01:06:05,300 --> 01:06:06,370
and I'll choose the other two.

1372
01:06:06,670 --> 01:06:09,970
No way. This trip
will be entirely up to you.

1373
01:06:09,970 --> 01:06:11,470
- Go wherever you want.
- What?

1374
01:06:12,310 --> 01:06:13,340
I'm home.

1375
01:06:13,570 --> 01:06:14,580
What?

1376
01:06:15,010 --> 01:06:16,980
It's not like our eldest
to get home from work on time.

1377
01:06:17,980 --> 01:06:19,010
Hey.

1378
01:06:19,680 --> 01:06:21,420
- I'm home.
- Sure.

1379
01:06:23,920 --> 01:06:25,220
That's odd.

1380
01:06:25,420 --> 01:06:27,560
Ji Wan and Su Bin
just got home as well.

1381
01:06:35,360 --> 01:06:37,470
Grandma has been eating her meals
and going to bed early.

1382
01:06:37,630 --> 01:06:38,630
It's not even that late.

1383
01:06:39,000 --> 01:06:40,370
That's how it gets with old age.

1384
01:06:40,840 --> 01:06:42,300
Your grandma is 88.

1385
01:06:47,310 --> 01:06:48,940
I have something to tell you.

1386
01:06:51,380 --> 01:06:53,550
I'm moving out.

1387
01:06:56,380 --> 01:06:58,390
What do you mean you're moving out?

1388
01:06:59,020 --> 01:07:01,860
As you can tell,
I'll be living on my own.

1389
01:07:02,760 --> 01:07:03,760
Ji Hyuk.

1390
01:07:05,790 --> 01:07:08,360
What nonsense is this?

1391
01:07:08,860 --> 01:07:10,930
Why would you move out
when you'll be getting married soon?

1392
01:07:11,630 --> 01:07:13,070
I don't plan on getting married.

1393
01:07:14,100 --> 01:07:15,640
What do you mean
you have no plans to marry?

1394
01:07:16,740 --> 01:07:18,210
What do you mean by that, Ji Hyuk?

1395
01:07:33,920 --> 01:07:35,090
Like I said,

1396
01:07:35,720 --> 01:07:37,590
I don't intend to marry anyone.

1397
01:07:39,190 --> 01:07:41,930
Hold on.
You're not planning to marry?

1398
01:07:42,260 --> 01:07:43,760
Isn't there someone you like?

1399
01:07:44,930 --> 01:07:46,130
There isn't.

1400
01:08:05,050 --> 01:08:07,990
(Value of Hangyeol)

1401
01:08:08,220 --> 01:08:09,920
(2016)

1402
01:08:16,900 --> 01:08:18,230
I won't fall in love
with anyone either.

1403
01:08:25,870 --> 01:08:26,910
I found her.

1404
01:08:30,640 --> 01:08:31,650
You did?

1405
01:08:35,780 --> 01:08:38,720
That's why I'm telling you
I'm moving out.

1406
01:09:26,370 --> 01:09:29,140
(Our Golden Days)

1407
01:09:29,500 --> 01:09:30,640
The second you move out,

1408
01:09:30,640 --> 01:09:32,810
you won't be able
to save up any money.

1409
01:09:32,810 --> 01:09:35,380
Ji Hyuk, does that mean
I can get married first?

1410
01:09:35,740 --> 01:09:38,780
What do you mean
it's advanced pancreatic cancer?

1411
01:09:39,110 --> 01:09:40,750
Ji Hyuk, did you hear the news?

1412
01:09:40,750 --> 01:09:42,220
What will happen to Dad?

1413
01:09:42,220 --> 01:09:44,850
Are you telling me to date a man
who's 17 years older than me?

1414
01:09:45,750 --> 01:09:49,090
Ji Eun Oh's been crushing
on Lee Ji Hyuk for a long time.

1415
01:09:49,890 --> 01:09:52,330
I wonder how that can benefit me.

1416
01:09:53,790 --> 01:09:56,100
What the... What are you doing here?

1417
01:09:56,100 --> 01:09:57,300
You told me to come.

1418
01:09:58,270 --> 01:09:59,770
I have feelings for you, Ji Hyuk.

